Package domain

Class Instructor

java.lang.Object
domain.Instructor
@Entity public class Instructor extends Object
This class extends the class Person and models Instructors, who hold Attractions (shows) in the zoo.

  • Constructor Details

    • Instructor

      public Instructor(String id, String firstName, String lastName, String password, List<Attraction> attractionsOfInstructor, double sum)
      Constructor - constructs and initializes an Instructor.
      Also uses the constructor from the class Person(super-class) for the attributes: username, firstName, lastName, password.
      Parameters:
      id - Instructor's id
      firstName - Instructor's firstname
      lastName - Instructor's lastname
      password - Instructor's passwords
      attractionsOfInstructor - list of Attractions which are held by the Instructor
      sum - income from the held Attractions (depends on the number of signed up Guests)

    • Instructor

      public Instructor(String id, String firstName, String lastName, String password)
      Constructor - constructs and initializes an Instructor without having previously assigned Attractions.
      List of Attractions is initially an empty list.
      Also uses the constructor from the class Person (super-class) for the attributes: username, firstName, lastName, password.
      Parameters:
      id - Instructor's id
      firstName - Instructor's firstname
      lastName - Instructor's lastname
      password - Instructor's password

    • calculateSum

      public void calculateSum()
      This method calculates and updates the income of the Instructor for the Attractions which he/she holds.
      The method adds the income from each Attraction.

    • toString

      public String toString()
      This method converts the Instructor object to a String.
      Returns:
      A String containing the ID, name and sum acquired from the held Attractions.
      Additionally, information is included about the hold Attractions:
      • Attraction name
      • day of Attraction
      • location
